docs.snippet: In a story Feb. 23 about a Southern California Gas Co. storage facility that leaked methane for nearly four months, The Associated Press erroneously reported the chief executive officer's last name. He is Dennis Arriola, not Dennis Arreola. And in...
docs.lead_paragraph: In a story Feb. 23 about a Southern California Gas Co. storage facility that leaked methane for nearly four months, The Associated Press erroneously reported the chief executive officer's last name. He is Dennis Arriola, not Dennis Arreola. And in stories on Jan. 28 and Feb. 2-4, The Associated Press erroneously reported the size of the leak. It released about 100,000 tons of methane, not more than 2 million tons.
